'password' => bcrypt('123456'),

 What is Hashing?
Hashing means converting a password into a secure encrypted string before storing it in the database.

Example:

Normal password

123456
Stored in database (hashed)

$2y$10$Xh3sD8sdfkj234ksdfjksdfkjsdfk
So if someone hacks the database, they cannot see the real password.

Why bcrypt() ?
Laravel uses bcrypt hashing algorithm.

bcrypt('123456')
It converts the password into a hashed value.

Better Laravel Way (Recommended)
Laravel officially recommends using Hash::make()

Add this at the top:

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Hash;
Then write:

'password' => Hash::make('123456'),
Example:

User::create([
    'name'=>'Admin',
    'email'=>'admin@gmail.com',
    'password'=>Hash::make('123456'),
    'is_admin'=>1
]);
